What a great little spot. Just randomly picked this spot to hang with a few friends and I was not disappointed! The bartender/waitress was bubbly, funny and very accommodating. Their cauliflower (Cauli Pau) is seriously some of the best I've ever had. 1 person had the Starr Burger and another had the Cauliflower burger. No complaints there, but the "starr" of the night was definitely the appetizers. We tried them all (cauliflower, potato croquettes and panipuri puffs) and they were amazing. Great music, cool vibes. This bar is a must visit if you're in the area. Restrooms: 1 in the bar area. 2 in the performance space area. Clean and good sized.

I was there last night for the Vibras NYC: Noche de los Santos event, so I'm giving it four stars solely because I really enjoyed that. The bar itself was okay. The girl behind the bar was not friendly and had an attitude any time we asked a question. Asked for a jack/coke and it was definitely overpoured. Asked for a "Chinga la Migra" as the menu said it was a sweet drink and it has got to be the most bitter drink I've ever had. Either there was definitely an ingredient missing from the drink which is why it was so bitter or the ingredients used were just old and rancid. Wouldn't go back for the drinks but would go back for another event like that one.

Shocking how one can let a man die on the sidewalk.  A middle aged man was passing out outside the bar, fainted from possible diabetic conditions. He asked to call an ambulance and while we waited for it, the man asked for water and I rushed to the bar to get it. The waitress first lied that they had no plastic containers, I had to point containers and cups at her. When I came back after 5min for another cup, she saw me and while she knew why I was here for, went on to serve another customer, then called me "sweetie" while pouring the cup, and didn't offer any additional help. This is when a human should get dismissed for actually doing executing their job scope blindly. Remember Eichmann's excuse? At any scale a human life is a human life.  This place is only suited for these hipsters I saw before me, passing by that fainted man who asked for an ambulance and water.  Let's always try to help each other, as one community!
